gw.bc.troubleticket.entity

Interface HoldRelatedEntity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bean, com.guidewire.commons.entity.BundleProvider, java.lang.Comparable<Bean>, com.guidewire.bc.domain.troubleticket.gen.HoldRelatedEntityStubI, IGosuObject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Account, com.guidewire.bc.domain.account.gen.AccountStubI, Policy, PolicyPeriod, com.guidewire.bc.domain.account.gen.PolicyPeriodStubI, com.guidewire.bc.domain.account.gen.PolicyStubI, Producer, com.guidewire.bc.domain.producer.gen.ProducerStubI

    public interface HoldRelatedEntity
extends com.guidewire.bc.domain.troubleticket.gen.HoldRelatedEntityStubI
    HoldRelatedEntity is a delegate representing an entity which can be the target of a hold (i.e., an Account, PolicyPeriod, or Producer). Specifically it is a single place where we can put implementation for hold-related functionality usable across Account/PolicyPeriod/Producer. For example implementation of a method that returns whether the Account/PolicyPeriod/Producer is currently the target of a specific type of hold.

    • Method Detail

      • isTargetOfHoldType

        boolean isTargetOfHoldType(HoldType holdType)
        Return true if the following two conditions are met: 1. This entity is associated with a Hold AND 2. The Hold has specified that the type of processing associated with the passed-in HoldType should be blocked
        Parameters:
        holdType - represents applying a hold to a particular type of automated processing (for example: automatic creation of Late Fees or automatic payment of Producer Commission)
        Returns:
        true if this entity is currently the target of a Hold AND the Hold has specified that the type of processing associated with the passed-in HoldType should be blocked

      • isImpliedTargetOfHoldType

        boolean isImpliedTargetOfHoldType(HoldType holdType)
        This method returns true if such an implied hold is currently targeting this entity (so for example, if this entity is an account that doesn't have any direct holds targeting it, if an invoice sending hold is targeting a child policy of this account then an implied hold is targeting this account)
        Parameters:
        holdType - type of hold
        Returns:
        true if this entity is being targeted by implication due to a hold against a child entity

      • isDirectOrImpliedTargetOfHoldType
